{
  "texts": [
    "Diagnosis represents the analytical process of categorizing psychological distress using established nosological systems such as the DSM-5 (American Psychiatric Association, 2022) and ICD-11 (World Health Organization, 2019).",
    "This involves differentiating normative emotional responses from pathological conditions while considering cultural (Teo, 2010) and developmental (Kawa and Giordano, 2012) variables that influence symptom manifestation.",
    "Significance.",
    "Diagnosis serves as the conceptual bridge between assessment and treatment, providing a structured framework for intervention planning (Jensen-Doss and Hawley, 2011).",
    "By aligning clinical observations with standardized criteria, it enhances communication among professionals (Craddock and Mynors-Wallis, 2014) and facilitates evidence-based decision-making (American Psychiatric Association, 2006)."
  ]
}